The paper proposes a novel graph neural network model for entity alignment in knowledge graphs. This involves encoding two KGs via multiple channels, which is a common approach in graph neural networks. The paper also discusses the use of self-attention and cross-KG attention, which are techniques commonly used in natural language processing and information retrieval. The paper also mentions the use of rule knowledge, which is a common approach in knowledge representation and reasoning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.DB (Databases). The paper also involves some natural language processing techniques, which suggests cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as possible sub-categories.
